init_text: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "This is the first time I've been able to get close enough."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They couldn't stand you and didn't want you around since your brother was more then happy to take over once he came of age.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He talked of how you were the true prince and his heir, but he had been ordered to leave you behind and he would never see you again.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You were the result of this union, and the queen had taken her anger out on you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The bees had been trying to get you to safety so that they could release your father, but every time they tried he would lose his memory of who

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: you and forget to watch out for you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They had gotten word that the queen would be away and you would be alone.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Today, they had finally stolen the queen's spell book.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Today was the day you became the bee king.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The bee on your shoulder told you to hold out your hand.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: you stood triumphant in front of your father, who was still trapped by the queen's spell.
